reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a toy that will stick around for a long time
reviews.reviewText: I recently had the pleasure of trying out the Diamond Magnetic Tiles 102pcs with Dolls, and let me tell you, it was an experience fit for royalty! These magnetic tiles are not your average building blocks. No, no! They come with a Frozen theme that will make any Frozen fan's heart melt with joy.First things first, the Frozen theme adds an extra layer of excitement to playtime. Kids can immerse themselves in the world of the movie and let their imaginations run wild. They can create their very own Frozen-inspired stories and scenes, building their own magical winter wonderland.But it doesn't stop there, my friends. These magnetic tiles also come with castle figures, including dolls, doors, windows, and stairs. Now your little princess can build her very own winter castle and kingdom. The parts are carefully designed and durable, ensuring hours of endless fun and imaginative play.Now, here's the real magic. Building with magnetic tiles isn't just about having fun; it's also a fantastic way to learn. These tiles provide an opportunity for kids to engage in STEM learning. They can experiment with balance, stability, and gravity as they build their structures. And let's not forget about the magnetic properties. Kids can learn about how magnets work and how they can be used to create amazing structures.With 102 pieces in the set, the possibilities are endless. These magnetic tiles are made of safe and durable ABS plastic, so you can rest assured that they are built to withstand the most enthusiastic builders. The magnets are strong, allowing for easy connection and stacking in various ways. Trust me; your little ones will be amazed at what they can create.And if you're wondering about the perfect birthday gift, look no further. The Diamond Magnetic Tiles are a surprising and delightful present that will leave kids speechless. It's not just a toy; it's a tool that encourages construction, creativity, and problem-solving skills. Plus, it provides hours of entertainment, giving parents some well-deserved peace and quiet.So, whether you have a little prince or princess in your life, the Diamond Magnetic Tiles 102pcs with Dolls are a must-have. They combine the enchantment of the Frozen theme, the thrill of building, and the joy of learning. It's a win-win for everyone involved. Trust me; you won't be disappointed with this gem of a toy!

reviews.reviewText: My daughter loves building with these, and loves that it came with two play people! reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Let me first say I purchased this for a 3 year old boy. I saw all the reviews saying that they purchased it for girls, but I couldn't see why because they are just tiles! My 3 year old and I love mixing this set with another one I have to build larger structures. I also think the steps, doors, and two tiny dolls are cute features.I will say that the label of 102 pieces can be deceiving as it comes with "windows" that you place inside of the tiles which seems to account for at least 60 of the 102 pieces. I purchased when it was a lightning deal, so I wasn't put off by the ratio of tiles to pieces. It is easy to put together, clean up, and a toddler can be very creative with the opportunity to incorporate the steps, fences, etc. Great purchase thay I would definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Magnetic building tiles are so much fun for a wide range of ages and this is such a pretty and fun set to use. I purchased the set for my 6 year old granddaughter, but all of the kids from 2-16 had a blast creating their own versions of the castle as well!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Must-have open-ended toy
reviews.reviewText: I don’t know why we slept so long on magnetic tiles (except for maybe the price of the name-brand ones), but our kids have been playing with these nonstop since Christmas…more so than anything else. They’re castles, spaceships, monsters, you name it. I will likely buy another set in the future to keep two kids quarrel-free. The colors are so pretty…it’s giving Frozen. The interchangeable doors and window pieces are cool too, giving bigger kids especially some neat options for constructing. Highly recommend…just consider a few sets for multiple kids!
